To generate a plant UML diagram, you can use the `@startuml` tag in JavaScript, which is essentially a text-based syntax editor where you write code with curly braces `{}`, and then run the code to produce a diagram that matches the input value. The `@enduml` tag then captures the output from the previous code execution into a single string (a single line) that represents the output node, along with any necessary data attributes.

Here is an example of how you can generate a plant UML diagram in JavaScript:
```javascript
const me = document; // Node to capture the input value
  @startuml {
    node.add(me); // Node with Name "value", Type "default" and Label "value", Type "default"
  }

  node.appendChild('label', 'type'); // Add label "type" to the node
  node.appendChild('data', 'value'); // Add value "value" to the node's data attribute
}
```
